In this article, President Donald Trump delivers remarks on immigration and the completion of the border wall during a visit to the Rio Grande Valley. He praises the men and women of Customs and Border Patrol and expresses his gratitude for their work on designing and constructing the wall. Trump emphasizes the importance of border security and the success of his administration in reducing illegal crossings and drug smuggling. He also highlights the reforms and agreements made with Mexico and the Northern Triangle countries to address asylum fraud and shared responsibility for immigration. Trump warns against reversing these measures, arguing that it would lead to a surge in illegal immigration and pose a threat to national security. He concludes by expressing his support for law enforcement and the need to uphold the rule of law in America.